description: Hongneung Arboretum is the first-generation arboretum in Korea. It was once the mausoleum of Empress Myeongseong, the concubine of King Gojong of the Joseon Dynasty. Hongneung Botanical Garden is a specialized botanical garden affiliated to the Korea Forestry Research Institute. It collects and manages the genetic resources of various domestic and foreign plants, and not only develops basic plant sciences, but also builds experimental research forests to secure plant genetic resources.
